<TextWithNodes><Node id="0" />GKN<Node id="3" />, the newly demerged automotive and aerospace group, <Node id="56" />yesterday<Node id="65" /> warned "life will get even tougher" after announcing first-half pretax profits had fallen by a quarter because of the <Node id="184" />US<Node id="186" /> economic slowdown.
<Node id="206" />Fearing a serious decline in <Node id="235" />Europe<Node id="241" /> - which is <Node id="253" />GKN<Node id="256" />'s main market - chief executive <Node id="289" />Marcus Beresford<Node id="305" /> said the short-term prospects for the big economies had rarely been so uncertain.<Node id="387" />

<Node id="389" />GKN<Node id="392" />, which folded its industrial services division into Australian group <Node id="462" />Brambles<Node id="470" /> earlier <Node id="479" />this week<Node id="488" />, is to axe up to a third of its 300 head office staff in a move that, with demerger costs, will impose an exceptional <Node id="607" />40m pounds<Node id="617" /> charge in the second half.<Node id="644" />

<Node id="646" />This could see the closure of its opulent <Node id="688" />London<Node id="694" /> head office in <Node id="710" />St James<Node id="718" />'s, with the only remaining headquarters sited in <Node id="768" />Redditch<Node id="776" />, <Node id="778" />West Midlands<Node id="791" />.<Node id="792" />

<Node id="794" />The group, which has already shed 700 jobs this year - 500 of them in the <Node id="868" />US<Node id="870" /> - reiterated fears that the <Node id="899" />13%<Node id="902" /> decline in <Node id="914" />US<Node id="916" /> motor output seen in the first half could soon spread to <Node id="974" />Europe<Node id="980" />. "We're not in the category of believing that something will suddenly come right," an unfazed <Node id="1075" />Mr Beresford<Node id="1087" /> said.<Node id="1093" />

<Node id="1095" />He added: "We are weathering these tough conditions pretty well and position ourselves for the upturn when it comes - as it surely will."<Node id="1232" />

<Node id="1234" />Such comments and the fact that the results - both for the consolidated group and its demerged successor - came in line with expectations left the market unconcerned as well, with <Node id="1414" />GKN<Node id="1417" /> shares, which started trading on <Node id="1451" />Tuesday<Node id="1458" />, up <Node id="1463" />6%<Node id="1465" /> at <Node id="1469" />296p<Node id="1473" />.<Node id="1474" />

<Node id="1476" />Mr Beresford<Node id="1488" /> even brushed aside worries that the group might exit the FTSE 100 at <Node id="1558" />next month<Node id="1568" />'s revision. "We've been in and out before; I don't mind in the least."<Node id="1639" />

<Node id="1641" />The automotive business, which raised turnover <Node id="1688" />10%<Node id="1691" /> in the first half despite problems in the <Node id="1734" />US<Node id="1736" />, accounts for <Node id="1751" />65%<Node id="1754" /> of <Node id="1758" />GKN<Node id="1761" />'s sales. <Node id="1771" />Mr Beresford<Node id="1783" /> expects European car output to be down just <Node id="1828" />1-2%<Node id="1832" /> at 16.4m - a sanguine view.<Node id="1860" />

<Node id="1862" />He admitted that the aerospace business - boosted by the <Node id="1919" />Agusta-Westland<Node id="1934" /> joint venture - could never offset the decline in the automotive division but said <Node id="2018" />GKN<Node id="2021" /> was less exposed to the cyclical downturn in aircraft production than its peers.<Node id="2102" />

<Node id="2104" />Â• <Node id="2106" />BAE Systems<Node id="2117" /> said it would cut 260 back-office posts at plants in <Node id="2171" />Warton<Node id="2177" /> and <Node id="2182" />Samlesbury<Node id="2192" />, <Node id="2194" />Lancashire<Node id="2204" />, in a "remodelling" of its business. But it would recruit 460 engineers between now the <Node id="2293" />end of the year<Node id="2308" />.<Node id="2309" /></TextWithNodes>
